@cbuescher This is a quite clever way to organize wildcard query!!! Good job here!!!
For this particular case of ? case, I think we need to add additional optional automata of PRERELEASE_SEPARATOR_BYTE and NO_PRERELEASE_SEPARATOR_BYTE.
Otherwise,  a query "1.2.3??" can't match  a version like "1.2.3+b" or a version like "1.2.3-a"

